        <div class="js-tweet-text-container">
  <p class="TweetTextSize TweetTextSize--normal js-tweet-text tweet-text" lang="en" data-aria-label-part="0">Local elections in May will decide how local services are run - and how much you pay for them. 

Things like street cleaning <img class="Emoji Emoji--forText" src="https://abs.twimg.com/emoji/v2/72x72/267b.png" draggable="false" alt="" title="Universal recycling symbol" aria-label="Emoji: Universal recycling symbol" />rubbish collection <img class="Emoji Emoji--forText" src="https://abs.twimg.com/emoji/v2/72x72/1f5d1.png" draggable="false" alt="" title="Wastebasket" aria-label="Emoji: Wastebasket" />road repairs <img class="Emoji Emoji--forText" src="https://abs.twimg.com/emoji/v2/72x72/1f697.png" draggable="false" alt="" title="Automobile" aria-label="Emoji: Automobile" />&amp; helping the elderly <img class="Emoji Emoji--forText" src="https://abs.twimg.com/emoji/v2/72x72/1f475.png" draggable="false" alt="" title="Older woman" aria-label="Emoji: Older woman" />

Conservative councillors deliver better services in your area and lower taxes for you.<a href="https://t.co/SBDbQ6XRBZ" class="twitter-timeline-link u-hidden" data-pre-embedded="true" dir="ltr">pic.twitter.com/SBDbQ6XRBZ</a></p>

Its only crime, moving a kerbstone. But Sheffields Labour council will soon rip it down. <span data-query-source="hashtag_click" class="twitter-hashtag pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr"><s>#</s><b>SaveSheffTrees</b></span> <span class="twitter-timeline-link u-hidden" data-pre-embedded="true" dir="ltr">pic.twitter.com/BPkBe8BCS9</span></div>

  <p class="TweetTextSize TweetTextSize--normal js-tweet-text tweet-text" lang="en" data-aria-label-part="0">My kid and two other students walked out of their rural, very conservative, public school for 17 minutes today. They were given two punishment options. They chose corporal punishment. This generation is not playing around. <a href="/hashtag/walkout?src=hash" data-query-source="hashtag_click" class="twitter-hashtag pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr"><s>#</s><b>walkout</b></a></p>

<div class="js-tweet-text-container">
  <p class="TweetTextSize TweetTextSize--normal js-tweet-text tweet-text" lang="en" data-aria-label-part="4">Not even one single child currently entitled to either free school meals or free childcare will lose that entitlement. Not one!!

Meanwhile MORE children will become eligible to receive that support due to these measures from Government.<a href="https://t.co/YQV83Bwaxb" rel="nofollow noopener" dir="ltr" data-expanded-url="https://twitter.com/FactCheck/status/965894977170665472" class="twitter-timeline-link u-hidden" target="_blank" title="https://twitter.com/FactCheck/status/965894977170665472"><span class="tco-ellipsis"></span><span class="invisible">https://</span><span class="js-display-url">twitter.com/FactCheck/stat</span><span class="invisible">us/965894977170665472</span><span class="tco-ellipsis"><span class="invisible"></span></span></a></p>

  <p class="TweetTextSize TweetTextSize--normal js-tweet-text tweet-text" lang="en" data-aria-label-part="0">The Womens Vote Centenary Grant Scheme is a 1.5 million government fund that will support local and community groups across England in celebrating the centenary of women gaining the right to vote. Find out more and submit your app here: <a href="https://t.co/8p6BPYEy0U" rel="nofollow noopener" dir="ltr" data-expanded-url="https://www.womensvotecentenaryfund.co.uk" class="twitter-timeline-link" target="_blank" title="https://www.womensvotecentenaryfund.co.uk"><span class="tco-ellipsis"></span><span class="invisible">https://www.</span><span class="js-display-url">womensvotecentenaryfund.co.uk</span><span class="invisible"></span><span class="tco-ellipsis"><span class="invisible"></span></span></a> <a href="/Baronessjenkin" class="twitter-atreply pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr" data-mentioned-user-id="334551644"><s>@</s><b>Baronessjenkin</b></a><a href="https://t.co/FVaszPHPXY" class="twitter-timeline-link u-hidden" data-pre-embedded="true" dir="ltr">pic.twitter.com/FVaszPHPXY</a></p>

  </ul>
</div>

        <div class="js-tweet-text-container">
  <p class="TweetTextSize TweetTextSize--normal js-tweet-text tweet-text" lang="en" data-aria-label-part="0">Diane Abbott proves again that Jeremy Corbyn's sums don't add up.   <p class="TweetTextSize TweetTextSize--normal js-tweet-text tweet-text" lang="en" data-aria-label-part="0">I'd like to thank the <a href="/hashtag/BBCQT?src=hash" data-query-source="hashtag_click" class="twitter-hashtag pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr"><s>#</s><b>BBCQT</b></a> audience for giving me a chance to make my case. Let's stay on the path to recovery, not go back to square one.</p>
</div>
